Kuroyu is the only establishment in Nyuto Onsenkyō that closes during the winter, as the other six inns operate year-round.

The onsen inspired {{ill|Yoshiharu Tsuge|ja|つげ義春|12=draft}}, a famous manga artist, who visited in May 1969 and September 1976. He depicted its atmosphere in four illustrations titled "Scenery of Travels" and "Tōgenkō." <ref>"[http://www.tsugeyoshiharu.com/makita2.html Traveling with Yoshiharu Tsuge]"</ref>

