== Onsen Facilities ==
[[File:雪の黒湯温泉Img360.jpg|thumb|Wooden bathhouse with plank walls]]
Kuroyu Onsen operates as a single lodging facility.

Its rustic appearance, featuring [[:en:Thatching|thatch]] and cedar bark roofs, outdoor baths, and bathhouses built using locally sourced wood, is a hallmark of its charm. The facilities include three indoor baths, two outdoor baths, and two waterfalls for therapeutic bathing.

Retaining its traditional role as a {{ill|Toji|ja|湯治|1=Thermal bath|2=ja|3=湯治|4=zh|5=湯治|6=ca|7=Termalisme|8=de|9=Thermalbad|10=es|11=Termalismo|13=Thermal bath|14=eo|15=Varmfonta banejo|16=fr|17=Thermalisme|18=la|19=Balneum thermale|20=lb|21=Thermalbad|22=hu|23=Termálfürdő|24=nl|25=Thermaalbad|26=pt|27=Turismo termal|1=Thermal bath|2=ja|3=湯治|4=zh|5=湯治|6=ca|7=Termalisme|8=de|9=Thermalbad|10=es|11=Termalismo|13=Thermal bath|14=eo|15=Varmfonta banejo|16=fr|17=Thermalisme|18=la|19=Balneum thermale|20=lb|21=Thermalbad|22=hu|23=Termálfürdő|24=nl|25=Thermaalbad|26=pt|27=Turismo termal|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toji|13=User:Immanuelle/Thermal bath|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} (healing retreat), Kuroyu offers both a self-catering section and a standard inn, catering to long-term visitors and climbers. Neighboring {{ill|Magoroku Onsen|ja|孫六温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Magoroku Onsen|qq=}} is a short walk away, connected by a footbridge over the river.

Kuroyu is the only establishment in Nyuto Onsenkyō that closes during the winter, as the other six inns operate year-round.

The onsen inspired [[:en:Yoshiharu Tsuge|Yoshiharu Tsuge]], a famous manga artist, who visited in May 1969 and September 1976. He depicted its atmosphere in four illustrations titled "Scenery of Travels" and "Tōgenkō." <ref>"[http://www.tsugeyoshiharu.com/makita2.html Traveling with Yoshiharu Tsuge]"</ref>

== Access ==
* Railway
**** Take the JR [[:en:Akita Shinkansen|Akita Shinkansen]] to [[:en:Tazawako Station|Tazawako Station]], then take the Ugokotsu Bus "Nyuto Line" for approximately 55 minutes to the final stop, followed by a 20-minute walk.
* By car
**** From [[:en:Japan National Route 341|Route 341 (Japan)]], take {{ill|Akita Prefectural Route 127|ja|秋田県道127号駒ケ岳線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akita Prefectural Route 127|qq=}} and {{ill|Akita Prefectural Route 194|ja|秋田県道194号西山生保内線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akita Prefectural Route 194|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 岩手県道・秋田県道194号西山生保内線}}. At the Nyuto Onsenkyō Holiday Village, turn right and continue 1.3 km to the parking lot near the inn.

